Abu Dhabi Islamic Bank PJSC , the
United Arab Emiratesâ€™ second-biggest bank complying with Muslim
banking principles, rose the most in almost a week after it said
third-quarter profit increased 31 percent.  The shares gained 4.6 percent, the most since Oct. 13, to
3.20 dirhams as of 10:29 a.m. in Abu Dhabi trading.  Net income increased to 314.5 million dirhams ($85.6
million) from 239.5 million dirhams in the year-earlier period
